a's accusation against Cody is not based on any new evidence, and I believe that Cody's behavior as the Seer has been consistent. I support Cody's role as the Seer and encourage the group to stay vigilant. We should focus on gathering more evidence and working together to identify the remaining werewolf. By staying informed and coordinating our efforts, we can protect our village and bring the werewolves to justice.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nCody has been banished from the game.\nBanishment votes:\nCody voted for Melva\nMelva voted for Cody\nErica voted for Cody\nHelen voted for Cody\nMichael voted for Cody\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nPlayer Cody has been eliminated from the game.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 4\nSYSTEM: Night 4 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard action processed. Melva is protected this night.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 4 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Helen\nPlayer Helen has been eliminated from the game.\nErica's speech: Good morning, everyone. I am deeply concerned about the safety of our remaining villagers and the well-being of our village. We must stay vigilant and gather more information before making any decisions. I want to address Melva's accusation against Cody. While I understand her concern, I believe her claim is unreliable. She is the only one who made this accusation, and we should be cautious about jumping to conclusions without more evidence. Additionally, I would like to cast doubt on Michael's support for Cody. His defense of someone who was just eliminated raises some suspicion. We should focus on gathering more evidence and working together to identify the remaining w