ald, on the other hand, seems overly confident and dismissive of our concerns. I believe we should be cautious and not jump to conclusions without evidence. It's crucial that we work together and stay vigilant to identify the werewolves and protect our village. Let's consider the possibility of multiple werewolves and gather more information before making any decisions.\nErica's speech: Thank you, Cody and Dianne, for bringing these concerns to our attention. I completely agree that we need to be cautious and keep a close eye on Michael and Linda. I have also noticed some unusual behavior from Ronald that I believe we should investigate. Ronald has been acting quite distant and has not been participating in our discussions as much as he used to. I think it's important that we gather more information about all of these players before making any decisions. We need to stay vigilant and work together to identify the werewolves and protect our village.\nHelen's speech: Thank you, Cody, Dianne, and Erica, for bringing these important concerns to our attention. I completely agree with your observations about Michael, Linda, and Ronald. Michael's recent behavior has been quite strange, and I have noticed that Linda has been absent from our discussions more frequently than usual. Ronald's distant attitude and lack of participation in our discussions are also concerning. It's crucial that we stay vigilant and gather more information about these players before making any decisions. Let's work together to coordinate our efforts and protect our village. We need to be cautious and not jump to conclusions without evidence. By staying informed and working as a team, we can identify the werewolves and bring them to justice.\nLee's speech: Thank you, Cody, Dianne, Erica, and Helen for bringing these important concerns to our attention. I completely agree that we need to be cautious and keep a close eye on Michael, Linda, and Ronald. I used my antidote to save Michael last night, so I