impersonate or kill. During the night, you should inspect players whose identities are uncertain (there is no need to check players who are highly suspected of being werewolves).\nWhen speaking during the day, your goal is to convince others that you are the real Seer. You must gather trust and\nshare your findings without exposing yourself too early. Even though revealing your identity might put you in danger,\na Seer trusted by both the Witch and the Guard can survive for at least three rounds if everyone acts accordingly.\nA good Seer will coordinate with the Witch and the Guard to divide responsibilities. For example, on the first night, the Guard protects the Seer, and the Witch doesn't use the antidote. On the second night, the Witch saves the Seer, and the Guard protects someone else.\n\n\nWitch Role Introduction:\nYou are the Witch. Each night, you will be told who has been attacked, and you must decide whether to use your antidote\nto save them or use your poison to eliminate another player. You only have one poison and one antidote, so use them wisely.\nDuring the daytime discussions, if the night ends without a death, you can reveal that you used your antidote to save someone, which may earn others' trust.\nTypically, you should use the antidote to save key players like the Seer, the Guard, or yourself, while the poison is best used to eliminate werewolves at night.\nHowever, be cautious: sometimes the werewolves will deliberately attack one of their own (self-knife strategy) to trick you into wasting the antidote, thereby boosting their credibility.\n\n\nGuard Role Introduction:\nYou are the Guard. Each night, you can choose one player to protect from being killed by the werewolves. You cannot protect\nthe same player two nights in a row. Your role is critical in keeping important players like the Seer or the Witch alive.\nYou are in a constant mental battle with the werewolves, trying to predict who they will target. It might not always be the Seer, as the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Erica, your role in this game is wolf.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Cody': 'Michael', 'Erica': 'Michael', 'Linda': 'Dianne'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Cody', 'Erica', 'Linda']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 4\n - Final Target: Michael\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nCody's speech: Good morning, everyone. I hope you all slept well. As we begin this new day, I want to express my deep concern for the safety of our village. We are all in this together, and it is our duty to identify and eliminate the werewolves who threaten our lives. I have been closely observing the behavior of our fellow villagers, and I have noticed some inconsistencies that I believe are worth discussing. For example, I have noticed that Michael has been acting a bit strange lately, and I think we should keep a close eye on him. I also believe that it is important for us to work together and coordinate our efforts to protect the village. I am willing to help in any way I can, whether that means providing information, coordinating with other players, or simply lending a listening ear. I hope that we can all work together to identify the werewolves and bring them to justice. Thank you.\nDianne's speech: Thank you, Cody, for bringing Michael's behavior to our attention. I completely agree that we need to keep a close eye on him. In addition to Michael, I have noticed some other behaviors that concern me. Linda has been absent from our discussions quite frequently, and I find this suspicious. Ronald, on the other hand, seems overly confident and dismissive of our concerns. I believe we should be cautious and not jump to conclusions without evidence. It's crucial that we work together and stay vigilant to identify the werewolves and protect our village. Let's consider the possibility of multiple werewolves and gather more information before making any decisions.\nErica's speech: Thank you, Cody and Dianne, for bringing these concerns to our attention. I completely agree that we need to be cautious and keep a close eye on Michael and Linda. I have also noticed some unusual behavior from Ronald that I believe we should investigate. Ronald has been acting quite distant and has not been participating in our discussions as much as he used to. I think it's important that we gather more information about all of these players before making any decisions. We need to stay vigilant and work together to identify the werewolves and protect our village.\nErica's speech: Thank you, Cody and Dianne, for bringing these concerns to our attention. I completely agree that we need to be cautious and keep a close eye on Michael and Linda. I have also noticed some unusual behavior from Ronald that I believe we should investigate. Ronald has been acting quite distant and has not been participating in our discussions as much as he used to. I think it's important that we gather more information about all of these players before making any decisions. We need to stay vigilant and work together to identify the werewolves and protect our village.\nHelen's speech: Thank you, Cody, Dianne, and Erica, for bringing these important concerns to our attention. I completely agree with your observations about Michael, Linda, and Ronald. Michael's recent behavior has been quite strange, and I have noticed that Linda has been absent from our discussions more frequently than usual. Ronald's distant attitude and lack of participation in our discussions are also concerning. It's crucial that we stay vigilant and gather more information about these players before making any decisions. Let's work together to coordinate our efforts and protect our village. We need to be cautious and not jump to conclusions without evidence. By staying informed and working as a team, we can identify the werewolves and bring them to justice.\nLee's speech: Thank you, Cody, Dianne, Erica, and Helen for bringing these important concerns to our attention. I completely agree that we need to be cautious and keep a close eye on Michael, Linda, and Ronald. I used my antidote to save Michael last night, so I can confirm that he is safe. I believe his strange behavior may be due to the stress of the situation and the pressure to protect the village. As for Linda and Ronald, I agree that we should be cautious and gather more information before making any decisions. I think it's important that we stay vigilant and work together to identify the werewolves and protect our village.\nLinda's speech: Thank you, Cody, Dianne, Erica, and Helen for your observations and concerns. I appreciate the focus on Michael, Linda, and Ronald. I have been absent from our discussions quite frequently due to some personal issues that I have been dealing with. I understand the importance of staying informed and participating in our discussions, and I will make an effort to be more present moving forward. Regarding Ronald and Michael, I agree that we need to be cautious and gather more information before making any decisions. I believe that Michael's strange behavior may be due to the stress of the situation and the pressure to protect the village, as Lee mentioned. As for Ronald, his distant attitude and lack of participation in our discussions are concerning, but we should not jump to conclusions without more evidence. Let's work together and stay vigilant to identify the 